{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3101"},"text":"§ 3101.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this chapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “best value” means, with respect to an acquisition, the optimal combination of cost, quality, technical capability or solution quality, and delivery schedule.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “capability requirement” means a capability that is critical or essential to address an operational problem.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “cost-effective” means, with respect to an acquisition, delivering superior end-user results at equal or lower cost compared to alternatives.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “operational problem” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bf9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a challenge of a military department in achieving an assigned military objective based on current doctrine, emerging threats, or future concepts; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bfa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may include limitations in capabilities, capacity, resources, or the ability to effectively and efficiently coordinate across the joint force, with another combatant command, or among military capabilities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bfb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “service chief” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bfc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Chief of Staff of the Army, with respect to matters concerning the Army;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bfd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Chief of Naval Operations, with respect to matters concerning the Navy;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bfe-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Commandant of the Marine Corps, with respect to matters concerning the Marine Corps;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2bff-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Chief of Staff of the Air Force, with respect to matters concerning the Air Force; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2c00-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3101/5/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Chief of Space Operations, with respect to matters concerning the Space Force.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa0a2c01-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/383/dA/tVIII/s861/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–383, div. A, title VIII, § 861(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-07"},"text":"Jan. 7, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/4288"},"text":"124 Stat. 4288","children":[],"tail":", § 2545; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tX/s1071/a/11"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title X, § 1071(a)(11)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3505"},"text":"128 Stat. 3505","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered